INGREDIENTS
2 tablespoons olive oil
~1 pound chorizo 
2 medium onions, chopped
2 large garlic cloves, minced
2 pounds sweet potatoes, quartered lengthwise, cut crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick slices
1 pound potatoes, halved lengthwise, cut crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick slices
6 cups chicken broth/stock 
1 9-ounce bag fresh spinach
PREPARATION
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat. 
Add sausage; cook until brown, stirring often, about 8 minutes. 
Transfer sausage to paper towels to drain. 
Add onions and garlic to pot and cook until translucent. 
Add potatoes and cook until they start to get soft
Add broth; bring to boil, scraping up browned bits. 
Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until potatoes are soft.
Using potato masher/immersion blender, mash/blend some of potatoes in pot. 
Stir the chorizo back in. 
Stir in spinach and simmer just until wilted.
Eat soup. 
